<a href="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=/8900/24.com/Web/DailySun/News/National_Article&sz=300x250&c=628573108&t=artid%3ddadeabc9-d5dd-4574-9eed-25ee7da8d8b1%26accreditation%3ddaily+sun%26posno%3d2" target="_blank"><img src="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=/8900/24.com/Web/DailySun/News/National_Article&sz=300x250&c=628573108&t=artid%3ddadeabc9-d5dd-4574-9eed-25ee7da8d8b1%26accreditation%3ddaily+sun%26posno%3d2" border="0" alt=""></a>Cops said the aim was to prevent the movement of drugs and stolen goods in and out of the area. Police spokesman Captain Nkosikho Mzuku told Daily Sun: “We conducted searches for illegal firearms, and to trace wanted suspects and illegal immigrants. “We also wanted to ensure that motorists don’t drink and drive at this time of the year.“Motorists must be warned that unannounced roadblocks will be held in the area.” Pamphlets with the 16 Days of Activism for no Violence against Women and Children message were also distributed at the roadblock.Motorists were urged to act against the abuse of woman and kids and not to look away. More than 100 vehicles were stopped via a trap camera focusing on outstanding warrants of arrest.Thirty drivers paid their outstanding traffic fines on the spot.Nineteen traffic fines were issued for overloading, driving without a driver’s licence and for driving unroadworthy vehicles. A 42-year-old suspect was arrested for outstanding traffic warrants. Three suspects were bust for contravening the immigration act.They will appear in the Mdantsane Magistrates Court soon.
